To build PyHEP (express version):

  ./configure --with-root=/path/to/root --with-cernlib=/path/to/cernlib
  make
  make install

Configure with --with-python to specify the Python installation to use.

By default, libraries are installed in the system-wide module directory
for the Python installation, "/usr/lib/python<version>/hep".

Use the "make-dist" script to build source and binary distribution. 

The "test" subdirectory contains regression tests.  Set your PYTHONPATH
to the "py" subdirectory of your build, and invoke "./test" to run
regression tests.  Specify the --stress option to include stress tests. 

------------------------------------------------------------------------

For usage information, see documentation generated in

  doc/pyhep.pdf
  doc/html/pyhep/index.html 

Documentation is installed by default in 
"/usr/share/doc/pyhep-<version>".

------------------------------------------------------------------------
